Bean Soup
  --Karlee Flores, Sur la Table

2 tbsp olive oil
1 medium yellow onion, chopped
2 red bell peppers, chopped
1 c celery, chopped
1 c carrots, chopped
2 zucchinis, chopped
1 c mushroom, chopped
1 tsp salt
1 tsp ground black pepper
1 can white beans
1 1/2 c corn
4 oz can green chilis
1 tbsp pollo seasoning
1 tbsp onion powder
1 tsp cumin
4 c chicken stock
1/2 c cilantro, chopped
juice of one lime
avocado for topping

Place a large Dutch oven over medium/high heat and drizzle in the olive oil. Add in the onion, bell peppers, carrots, zucchini, and mushrooms all at once. Sprinkle in the salt and pepper and saut√© together, mixing frequently until the vegetables have sweat and shrunk by ~half. Add in the beans, corn, green chili, pollo seasoning, onion powder, and cumin. Mix together and cook for another 2 min. Add in the chicken stock, cover and let simmer until the vegetables are soft but not mushy, ~5 min. Remove from the heat and add the cilantro and lime juice. Serve with fresh avocado.

